A role for @COMPOUND$ and @PROTEIN$ combination in protecting from liver injury in a model of type 2 diabetes with hyperlipidemia.

Genetic type 2 diabetic Goto-Kakizaki rats were fed with a high-fat diet to test hepatic effects of type 2 diabetes with hyperlipidemia and the effect of @COMPOUND$ and @PROTEIN$, individually and in combination, in systemic and hepatic inflammatory and oxidative stress markers.
Combination of @PROTEIN$ and @COMPOUND$ further improved glycemic and lipid profiles and decreased circulating C-reactive protein levels and liver inflammatory and oxidative stress markers.

@PROTEIN$ and @COMPOUND$ combination leads to better glycaemic and lipid profiles and to better protection against liver inflammation and oxidative stress, giving a superior level of liver protection in type 2 diabetic with hyperlipidemia.
